# ========================================
# Security Notes
# ========================================
#
# ⚠️ IMPORTANT SECURITY GUIDELINES:
#
# 1. Client-Side Only: All VITE_* variables are exposed to the client.
#    Never put sensitive data (API secrets, private keys) here.
#
# 2. Public Tokens: Shopify Storefront tokens are designed to be public
#    and have read-only permissions. This is safe.
#
# 3. Supabase Anon Key: The "anon" key is public and safe for client-side.
#    Row-Level Security (RLS) protects your data in Supabase.
#
# 4. Server-Side Secrets: For server secrets (admin tokens, webhook secrets),
#    configure them in:
#    - Supabase Dashboard → Settings → Secrets (for Supabase Functions)
#    - Lovable Dashboard → Settings → Environment Variables (server-side only)
#
# 5. Version Control: Add .env and .env.production to .gitignore
#
# 6. Team Access: Share credentials securely (1Password, LastPass, etc.)
#
# ========================================

# ========================================
# Verification Checklist
# ========================================
#
# Before deploying to production, verify:
#
# [ ] All required variables are set (no "your-xxx-here" placeholders)
# [ ] Supabase project ID matches your production project
# [ ] Supabase URL matches the project ID
# [ ] Supabase anon key is correct (test with API call)
# [ ] Shopify store domain is correct (without https://)
# [ ] Shopify storefront token has read access (test product fetch)
# [ ] Shopify API version is current and supported
# [ ] VITE_SITE_URL points to production domain (with https and www)
# [ ] All URLs use https:// (not http://)
# [ ] No sensitive/private keys are included
# [ ] File is NOT committed to Git (.gitignore should block it)
#
# ========================================

# ========================================
# Quick Start
# ========================================
#
# 1. Development:
#    cp env.main-site.example .env
#    # Edit .env with your dev credentials
#    npm run dev
#
# 2. Production:
#    cp env.main-site.example .env.production
#    # Edit .env.production with production credentials
#    # Push to main branch - Lovable auto-deploys
#
# 3. Verify:
#    npm run build && npm run preview
#    # Test locally before deploying
#
# ========================================

# ========================================
# Troubleshooting
# ========================================
#
# Q: Changes not reflected in browser?
# A: Restart dev server (Ctrl+C, then npm run dev)
#
# Q: "Supabase client not initialized" error?
# A: Check VITE_SUPABASE_URL and VITE_SUPABASE_PUBLISHABLE_KEY are set
#
# Q: Products not loading from Shopify?
# A: Verify VITE_SHOPIFY_STOREFRONT_TOKEN has read permissions
#
# Q: CORS errors?
# A: Ensure Shopify store has correct storefront API permissions
#
# Q: Environment variables undefined in code?
# A: Use import.meta.env.VITE_* to access (not process.env)
